					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 12 <hi rend="italic">sirīyakki-paḻañjalāgai achchu</hi> for feeding of <hi rend="italic">āṇḍārs</hi> (devotees) by a certain Mutti Āṇḍi Ammai, wife of a merchant named Piḷḷān of Karaiyānaḍikkīḻtaḷam in Vaḍaparisāra-nāḍu. One <hi rend="italic">nāḻi</hi> rice per <hi rend="italic">achchu</hi> was to be supplied for this purpose.</p>						

						</summary>
